
[1]denunciation

   DENUNCIATION, n.

   1. Publication; proclamation; annunciation; preaching; as a faithful
   denunciation of the gospel.

   2. Solemn or formal declaration, accompanied with a menace; or the
   declaration of intended evil; proclamation of a threat; a public
   menace; as a denunciation of war, or of wrath.
